pr_review_comment_body:
@fenglu-g Can do that. But do you want me to replace `labels=None` to `labels={'airflow-version': 'v' + version.replace('.', '-').replace('+', '-')})` or update whatever labels are passed with `labels.update({'airflow-version': 'v' + version.replace('.', '-').replace('+', '-')}))`

My only concern is some companies have a strict policy for using labels to track their pricing and already have a naming convention set for their labels. 

What's your suggestion? Should we be passing the `airflow-version` label if no labels are passed or just add this key to whatever labels they pass?

yes, it return unicode string before:
```
    def _absolute_path(self, path):
        path = path.encode(self._encoding)
        if not self._is_windows_path(path):
            path = self._client.normalize(path)
        if not isinstance(path, unicode):
            path = unicode(path, self._encoding)
        return path
```
for javaclient:
```
    def _absolute_path(self, path):
        return self._client.canonicalPath(path)
```

this is almost the same in the other distros, except for the packages that are split differently.

Would it be better if something does the work of intersecting the lists to determine the packages needed? It seems that
they all follow the same pattern, except for the change of items that pull in the ceph package. So something like:

    packages = set()
    for c in ceph_components:
        if c in components:
            components.remove(c)
            packages.append('ceph')

    for c in components:
        packages.append(c)

    return list(packages)

Would allow us to just define what the `ceph_components` are (mind you I didn't put much thought in naming) and the helper would get the same results.

@gsalgado I finally found something to improve that. The trick was to break down the initialization of the dict from the `get(...)` call so that I could add annotations for the `Dict`. (if we didn't have to use comment annotations this could be written without breaking it apart).

https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/pull/459/commits/27a694dfdb8e3d1422d73dc678ab02e5c0eb20ce

It's still not perfect but at least it allows us to get rid of the mypy silencing. Anyway, no need to review/merge just yet. I'll again batch a couple of changes for the next PR.
